tip.text: epic Ethiopian. wonderful, fresh injera, tasty sauces (which are topped up if you want more) and an all over good vibe.
wonderful hideout for organic and vegan food and patting the cafe cat.
Fantastic flavours from foraged and locally produced ingredients. Each dish is pure joy to tastebuds. The time between dishes was at times 45mins - still one of my top food experiences this year.
Cozy, relaxed and tasty dining in Katajanokka's newest shelter spot by the sea. Good wine picks and a few alternating craft beers. Go late in the evening and book a candlelit corner table.
great last stop for a mountain trek in Sarek. amazing restaurant and comfy beds. highly recommended.
Cozy little piece of California in Signaghi. Homemade, scrumptious tex mex full of flavour. Take a seat in the back, the view of Alazani valley is stunning .
lovely place. homemade lemonade, sulguni in yoghurt and vegetables with walnuts were divine.
i cried a little when I had a bite of their pizza. tangy fresh tomato sauce and a whole lotta wonderful cheese. recommend to call and order in advance!
laidback neighbourhood gastropub. the antipasto plate with roquefort, chechili, merguez, hummus, tapenade, truffle mayo etc is impeccable!
good getaway for georgian grub such as khachapuri and khinkali.
seriously one of the best Nepalese in Helsinki. Worth the trip. Fresh as damn.
top notch burger. better than most in town. well worth the trip, which is literally just a couple of tube stops from the center. the truffel mayo rocks socks.
Rare opportunity to have yum natural wines and great midnight bites in Helsinki. Try the lemon risotto, tartar and tomato-ginger pappardelle.
fantastic fresh vegan food with delicate flavours. loved the lentil balls with tahini sauce and feta-sprout-almond salad.
Beautifully renovated residential palace turned restaurant. Unfortunately the really gorgeous setting does not make the 39€ substandard brunch any less of a rip-off.
Charming interior, food and service. Great wines sold by the cl - you can sample as many as you like. The bluecheese soup with escargots was magnifique.
Delicious, freshly made vietnamese dishes (Bun bo, Pho) for 8-10€. They even do home-delivery (!) Highly recommendable.
Cute homemade sushi takeaway/dine-in at the foot of a residential house in Käpylä. Started off at Restaurant Day, now open weekday evenings 16-19 and Saturdays. Try the unagi!
Best summer rolls in town, loaded with fresh mint. But don't be fooled by having just them - the menu is packed with good vietnamese dishes. Reasonable prices and nice staff too. What's not to love?
Cheese and charcuterie platter with a glass of Amarone 5/5.
super cozy pizzeria tucked away in a not-likely neighbourhood. pulcino pizza with pear, gorgonzola and walnuts = 5/5. love the margherita too!
Delicious christmas buffet, best in town. The xmas decor is hardcore and will make you in the holiday mood, fo' shizzle!
sympathique hidden bistro with comfort food and a couple of lovely italian white wines.
outstanding tapas. licked all of the plates.
this great pub hosts different pop up restaurants depending on the day. enjoy with draft beer from small Czech breweries.
terrific whiskey ice-cream.
